<title><![CDATA[It’s  and I had the honor of speaking at an AFTD fundraiser on Monday. My mom was diagnosed with frontotemporal dementia almost 4 years ago, and it’s such a cruel disease. It took me a long time to look into a support group for family members of those with FTD, but if you’re going through this too, just know you’re not alone and there are lots of online and in person meet ups to find some comfort. Theaftd.org is a great resource for learning more about the disease and finding ways to volunteer, as well ❤️]]></title>
<link>https://v16m-default.tiktokcdn-us.com/bd15b1048359af23e6f7dc2701688c4f/670dc8b0/video/tos/useast5/tos-useast5-ve-0068c002-tx/o0D1jNFw6HEEImAnHAIejpefnNBA6FQDgMkCgy/?a=1988</link>
